parameters:
Is that the truth!? Are you saying that the goods you're
dealing with are the ores dug up by the laborers in that
mine...!?
Dealer: Eek! Stop it! No violence, please!

No violence, you say!? Which mouth of yours is spouting
those words!! Do you have any idea how many people have
suffered violence in the mines because of you!!
Dealer: I-I don't know...! I was just following orders.

Dealer: Sure, I might've bought some people off and made
them work in the pits, but what choice did I have!

Dealer: It's a deal from the high officials of the royal
capital. Once you hear about it, a small-time crook like me
would just get snuffed out if I refused!

From the high officials of the royal capital, you say!?
Nonsense!? Who is it! If you know, then say their name!

Then what is the purpose of that mine!? Where is it being
transported to, and what are they planning to do with it!?

Dealer: Don't ask everything all at once, I'll tell you what
I know...!

Dealer: First off, I might've said something earlier, but to
be honest, I don't know specifically who I'm dealing with.

Dealer: But piecing together the information that leaks from
the petty complaints of the low-level thugs I meet at the
deal site, it's a safe bet they're operating under the
orders of some big shot from the royal capital.

Dealer: And as for what's being taken from the mine and what
it is, I don't know that either. It's just a hole we dug
following the instructions of our trading partners. The
management... well, let's just say I left it to an idiot.

Watch your mouth... You're only safe right now because you
still have information that needs to be spilled. Be aware of
that and speak accordingly...

Dealer: Ughh!! If you hit me like that, I won't be able to
talk!
Hurry up and continue.

Dealer: The goods we had dug up in the mining quarry are
crystals, as you know. But they seem to be a bit special,
unlike normal stones, they're said to be highly concentrated
with magical power.

Dealer: Apparently, they're using them like crazy in some
kind of experimental facility where they need them in large
quantities. They'll buy as much as we can provide. It was
such a profitable job it made all my previous dealings look
like child's play.

Dealer: That's not all. In addition, workers who became
useless in the mines were also taken off our hands for a
price.

Dealer: They'd buy them all up because they use everything
as materials for experiments. The guys I'm dealing with are
involved in some shady stuff that probably makes what I do
look cute in comparison.
──...When is your next transaction taking place?
